# Purpose of sanitizers
 AddressSanitizer (ASan) is a memory error detector
  See more: https://github.com/google/sanitizers/wiki/AddressSanitizer
 LeakSanitizer (LSan) is a memory leak detector which is integrated into AddressSanitizer.
  See more: https://github.com/google/sanitizers/wiki/AddressSanitizerLeakSanitizer
 UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer (UBSan) is a fast undefined behavior detector.
  See more: https://clang.llvm.org/docs/UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer.html

# docs: https://github.com/google/sanitizers
# install: https://apt.llvm.org

# How to use
 Create a build folder and jump into it:
  $ mkdir build && cd "$_"
 Set env variables:
  $ export SANITIZER=ASAN (or LSAN, UBSAN)
 Run the script:
  $ facelift/tests/sanitizers/test_sanitizers.sh
